features: LAURA GELLER NEW YORK BEST OF THE BEST TUSCAN DREAMS FULL FACE MAKEUP PALETTEThis complete eye and face makeup palette includes six baked eyeshadows in beautiful neutral tones, a Baked Bronze-n-Brighten in Roman Holiday, a Baked Natural Glow Highlighter in French Vanilla and a Baked Blush-n-Brighten in Starfish Island.

INCLUDES BLUSH, BRONZER, HIGHLIGHTER, AND EYESHADOW: These goodies are truly the best of our best! This all-in-one full face palette is the perfect introduction to our famous baked beauty. It includes a blush, bronzer, highlighter and six nude eyeshadows.

HANDMADE IN ITALY: Baked makes it better. Every formula in this eyeshadow, blush and highlighter palette starts out as a cream before being baked into a silky powder on terracotta tiles. Everything is artisan-made by hand in Italy.

FEATURES BOTH MATTE AND SHIMMER SHADES: Imagine, an Italian getaway in one makeup palette. Inspired by the colors of a dreamy Tuscan escape, this palette is filled with Laura Geller’s fan favorite shades, including matte and shimmer finishes.

HOW TO APPLY:Eyeshadows: Apply all over the lid. Use darker shades to define in the crease and blend lighter shades on browbone as a highlight., Highlighters: Dust across the tops of the cheekbones, down the bridge of the nose, and on the Cupid’s bow, Blush: Apply to apples of the cheeks for a fresh pop of color, Bronzer: Sweep all over your face to warm up your complexion or contour along the temples, hollows of the cheeks, and jawline for a more sculpted look.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not all that
reviews.reviewText: I wanted to update my makeup and I heard good things about this brand and thought I would give it a try. I like that it comes as a combo but over all I was not really that impressed with the highlight powder, bronzer and blush.I use a light coverage CC cream daily and I just wanted something to 'glam it up' a little. But what I got was not what I was going for.It looked heavy on my skin - the blush made me look 'clownish' and created a harsh line that didn't want to blend- I had to dab my face with a washcloth too get it to tone down.The highlighter is pretty, but be careful where you put it - too much on the forehead and you will look like a lighthouse. And the bronzer - had me looking all 2001 - back when bronzer first hit the scene and everyone looked sunburned, terra cotta, or burnt orange. Yes - that's what I looked like. So be feather light with your application to avoid these mishaps.The eye shadows are pretty and I do use those, but they would be better off in a smaller size on their own or add a couple more. I know they are heavily pigmented but they are very small. Especially when compared to the negative space left in the pallet. Yes, I saw the photo - it gives the illusion that you are getting a lot - it's bulky for that reason. There's enough room for 2 more powders or more eye shadows, easily.Overall - I doubt I will purchase any more products from this brand before I see it or sample it first.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not good for me.
reviews.reviewText: I’m always looking for that perfect product for the senior adult skin. I have seen so many commercials about this makeup that says it does not get into your creases and wrinkles. I was a little surprised that it is a powder and powders do just that… they accentuates wrinkles , and it’s not particularly attractive on older dry skin. This product is a heavy powder. The eye shadows alone might be okay but no… overall, I was very disappointed and am sending it back.
